### 3. File System Access API (Alternative)

**Documentation:** [The File System Access API | Chrome for Developers](https://developer.chrome.com/docs/capabilities/web-apis/file-system-access)

**Browser Support:**
- ✅ Chrome/Chromium (Windows, macOS, ChromeOS, Linux, Android)
- ❌ Firefox (not supported)
- ❌ Safari (not supported)
- ⚠️ Brave (behind flag)

**Capabilities:**
- User grants access via file picker
- Can read/write files on device
- Requires user gesture + secure context (HTTPS)

**Why NOT for Bookmark Sync:**
1. **User must manually select file** (defeats purpose of auto-sync)
2. **Read-only for bookmarks** (no write-back to browser)
3. **Chrome-only** (Firefox/Safari not supported)
4. **Security:** Browser bookmark files may be locked while browser running
5. **Complexity:** Different file formats (Chrome JSON vs Firefox SQLite)

**Sources:**
- [The File System Access API | Chrome for Developers](https://developer.chrome.com/docs/capabilities/web-apis/file-system-access)
