## Implementation Approaches

### Approach 1: Browser Extension with IndexedDB Sync (RECOMMENDED)

**Architecture:**

```
Browser Bookmarks (Native)
    ↓ (Extension reads via chrome.bookmarks API)
Browser Extension (Background Worker)
    ↓ (Processes & formats)
    ↓ (Sends via chrome.runtime.sendMessage)
Content Script (Injected in neuman.dev)
    ↓ (Forwards via window.postMessage)
Neuman Brain Web App
    ↓ (Receives & validates)
IndexedDB (Link Library Store)
```

**Components:**

1. **Browser Extension**
   - Manifest V3
   - Background service worker
   - Content script injected into Neuman Brain domain
   - Permissions: `"bookmarks"`, `"storage"`, host permission for neuman.dev

2. **Background Worker** (extension)
   - Listens for bookmark events (onCreate, onRemove, onChange)
   - Periodically fetches full bookmark tree
   - Formats bookmarks into NB-compatible structure
   - Sends to content script

3. **Content Script** (extension)
   - Injected into Neuman Brain web app
   - Bridges extension ↔ web page
   - Uses window.postMessage for communication
   - Validates messages (origin check)

4. **Neuman Brain Web App** (existing)
   - Listens for postMessage events
   - Validates extension messages
   - Writes bookmarks to IndexedDB
   - Updates Link Library UI

**Sync Strategy:**
- **One-Way:** Browser → Neuman Brain (for MVP)
- **Real-Time:** Bookmark events trigger immediate sync
- **Periodic:** Full sync every 5 minutes (catch missed events)
- **Two-Way (Future):** NB can write back to browser via extension

**Pros:**
✅ Native API access (fast, reliable)
✅ Real-time sync via event listeners
✅ Cross-browser (Chrome, Firefox, Edge)
✅ No cloud required (local-first)
✅ User controls extension install
✅ Can add two-way sync later
✅ No file system complexity

**Cons:**
❌ Requires extension installation
❌ Extension store approval process (1-2 weeks)
❌ Maintenance across 3 browsers
❌ User must grant permissions

**Development Effort:** ~40 hours
- Extension: 20 hours (background worker, content script, manifest)
- Web app integration: 8 hours (postMessage handler, IndexedDB sync)
- Testing: 8 hours (Chrome, Firefox, Edge)
- Documentation: 4 hours (user guide, privacy policy)

**Privacy:**
✅ No data sent to servers
✅ Direct browser → NB communication
✅ Open source (users can audit)
✅ Optional feature (users opt-in)

